The plaid pattern itself is bold and geometric, featuring interlocking triangles or diamonds that represent the strength and unity of their community. To add a touch of magic, metallic threads are woven into the fabric to catch the light and sparkle like the precious stones that the Oread people mine from their mountain homes.
